{
  "texts": [
    "The substrate potential ∆(r) varies with x 1 along the a 1 direction, but is uniform along the a 2 direction.",
    "The sign-changing potential divides the system into L and R regions, and can generate two sets of Chern or valley DWs due to the periodic boundary conditions.",
    "We schematically illustrate the case of Chern DWs which host co-propagating chiral modes.",
    "Green envelope represents a hybrid Wannier state |W K τ as ⟩ which is exponentially localized along a 1 but extended along a 2 (note that the actual wavefunction amplitude will vary along a 2 according to the moiré periodicity).",
    "(b) Phase diagram of the energy competition between Chern DWs and valley DWs as a function of twist angle θ and substrate potential gradient ∆max/w."
  ]
}